<br>
Go get your boots.  You need to pick up 2 items in kith.  One you need to take to lake rathe to get a diferent item.<br>
There is some cost to the quests, normally you need an enchanter platnium bar.  Save them pp (105pp each with good cha), and find a 34th+ lvl enchanter friend (guildmate?) to enchant them for you.  <br>
Legs, easy.  Pick up one item in upper guk.  What race are you?  Long as not dark elf, you should not be kos in upper guk.  The second piece you will have to kill an eruite in kerra ridge.  Not sure its level, go check it out.  Can always bring a friend later.<br>
<br>
Point being most of the cleric quests are fairly simple (time and some pp that hard part).  A few of them are rather tough, and you need to act safely, or get a higher level friend to help you out.<br>
<br>
If you haven't done so, concentrate on your wisdom gear.  Better earings and rings.  Maybe a wisdom veil.  I know they take some coin, but if you have the coin, they are usually easy to find. (seek your enchanter friend again).<br>
<br>
Just some advice from you local cleric armor questing wizard.<br>
(I do the quests whenever I am in zone with an item, so I may donate to the guild).<br>
Lazzari V Tempest<br>
